commitResults.messageBody:
Commands did not have assertions to ensure code quality

Add assertions to check that arguments and local variables are not null

This is to ensure that methods and properties will not be invoked on null
objects, which will cause exceptions

AddDeadlineCommand had unnecessary methods and unclear variable names

Remove equals method and changed task variable from 't' to 'task'

Done to improve readability and remove clutter from code

commitResults.messageTitle: Add equals method to task commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Equals method was removed earlier as it was thought to be unnecessary. However,
it is needed for testing purposes so that JUnit can assert equality of outputs from
parser.

Add equals method from older commits and improve code quality by refactoring

The previous equals methods worked well, but had long boolean expressions.

Code quality needs to be improved for better readability. Variable names were unclear and certain lines were
just multiple method calls.

Break down complicated expressions into steps and improve variable names

By implmenting these changes, the code will be easier to read for future development
